The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring November 15, 2013, as America Recycles Day. The proclamation highlights the importance of recycling in reducing pollution, saving energy, preserving raw materials, and reducing greenhouse gas emissions. It also emphasizes the economic benefits of recycling and encourages individuals, schools, and communities to make recycling a part of their daily lives. The proclamation calls for appropriate programs and activities to observe America Recycles Day and encourages continued efforts in reducing, reusing, and recycling throughout the year.